# Heartbeat Template — meshterm Message Polling
#
# Copy this to your OpenClaw heartbeat config and customize.
# The heartbeat runs on a schedule and checks for new messages.

## Heartbeat Action

```bash
# Poll meshterm for unread messages
MESSAGES=$(meshterm poll 2>&1)

if echo "$MESSAGES" | grep -q "No unread"; then
  exit 0
fi

# Messages found — relay to user or process
echo "$MESSAGES"
```

## Schedule

Run every 30-60 seconds for near-real-time message delivery.
For true real-time, configure the webhook instead (see SKILL.md).
